<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17181] camel-core - XPathBuilder never clears pool when using @XPath annotation and grows pool causing memory leak</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17181</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using &lt;b&gt;@XPath()&lt;/b&gt; annotations to bean method parameters, &lt;b&gt;XPathBuilder&lt;/b&gt; is used and expressions are added to a pool in the &lt;b&gt;init()&lt;/b&gt; method of the class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These expressions are keep adding up but they are never cleared.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a method &lt;b&gt;doStop()&lt;/b&gt; which has the code for cleaning but it is never used, hence a leakage of XPathExpressions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
